# Default Git Workflow: Feature Branch + PR to `main`

Assistants use this for **any** repo change **by default**. **Throughput / urgency from the user does not waive** the **Bot feedback wait gate** or in-thread replies—see **`.cursor/rules/workflow-rules-never-overridden.mdc`**. GitHub automation naming: **`docs/CONCURRENT_AGENT_WORKFLOW.md`**.

## Required pattern

1. `git fetch origin` → checkout **`main`** → `git pull origin main`.
2. `git checkout -b agent/<slug>` (or **`feat/`** / **`fix/`**). One branch per task/agent stream.
3. Commit **only** on that branch; `git push -u origin HEAD`.
4. Open PR to **`main`** (`gh pr create --base main` or UI).
5. Keep pushing until **`ci_result`** passes. **Green CI is necessary, not sufficient** for merge.
6. **`pr-auto-merge.yml`** may enable squash auto-merge for heads whose names start with **`agent/`**, **`feat/`**, or **`fix/`** (i.e. glob **`agent/*`**, **`feat/*`**, **`fix/*`**), when **`ci_result`** is green—**bot apps are not in that gate**. Complete **PR review bots** (below) **before** first-time auto-merge so CI cannot merge unanswered threads. If auto-merge is unavailable: fix forward or `gh pr merge --squash`—**still only after the wait gate**. **`stale-branch-cleanup.yml`** trims stale topic remote heads (see **`docs/CONCURRENT_AGENT_WORKFLOW.md`**).

### Same PR for follow-up (bots, CI, E2E, rollout)

Fix on the **open** branch; do **not** open a second PR for the same deliverable unless directed. After fixes, PR comment or in-thread **`@mention`** using **`@login`** handles from **`gh pr view -c`** (not workflow display names).

### Bot feedback wait gate (hard)

Manual **`gh pr merge`** or **enabling** squash auto-merge is **forbidden** until this completes, unless the human **explicitly waives bot closeout for that PR** in writing.

1. **`gh pr checks <n> --watch`** green (`ci_result` + required checks).
2. **Stop**—do not merge in the same breath as CI success.
3. **Late-review sweep:** `gh pr view <n> --comments`; optionally `gh api repos/<owner>/<repo>/pulls/<n>/reviews` and `gh api repos/<owner>/<repo>/pulls/<n>/comments`. On **github.com**, scan Conversation + Files for **in-flight** bot activity (reactions, pending review); wait until **settled**. Note bots **after** your last push (Gemini, Copilot, Codex, CodeRabbit, Greptile, Sourcery, scanners, etc.).
4. If **no** substantive threads yet: wait **~10–15 minutes** from first green CI, re-sweep (and re-check UI). Calling “no feedback” immediately at green CI is a **policy violation**.
5. **Enumerate → judge → reply in-thread** on every substantive thread: **implemented** / **deferred** / **declined** (with reason).
6. **Only then** merge or enable auto-merge **for the first time**.
7. If you cannot finish 3–6: leave PR open + **PR URL** + remaining steps—do not merge “to save time.”
8. **After merge:** `npm run git:graph-hygiene` (or `git fetch origin --prune`); delete local topic branch when safe (**`docs/CONCURRENT_AGENT_WORKFLOW.md`**).
9. **Production closeout:** after **`main`** + deploys—**`AGENTS.md`**, **`every-chat-commit-deploy-verify-production.mdc`**. CI ≠ live-site sign-off; **`test:homepage`** may fail on headless cloud runners.

## PR review bots (before squash merge to `main`)

Treat automated reviewers **like humans** for **substantive** feedback (behaviour, correctness, security, architecture, enforced-policy hygiene—not trivial spelling unless meaning changes).

- **Reply in-thread** for each thread—**not** only commits. After a fix: short reply (+ SHA optional). Defer/decline: say why in-thread.
- **`ci_result` + auto-merge** = when GitHub *may* merge; **policy** = threads closed with visible replies **before** you merge or enable auto-merge.

Do **not** merge with substantive threads unanswered.

## Exceptions (narrow)

- User explicitly **`main`** hotfix: push **`main`**, still production closeout after deploy.
- Already on a named feature branch: continue there; rebase/merge **`origin/main`** if stale.
- **Written** waiver of bot closeout **for that PR**: may merge/skip gate **for that PR only**.

## Do not

- Call feature-branch push **“shipped”** for www until merged to **`main`** and hosting finished (unless checking **Pages preview** only).
